                     <interp inst="t18430821-2587-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18430821-2587-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp> for a like offence.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1850" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1850" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1850" type="surname" value="COOMBE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1850" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM COOMBE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a licensed victualler. The prisoner came to me on the 2nd of August for a pint of beer, and tendered me a counterfeit shilling—I said that sort would not do for me, it was a bad one—I cut it asunder, gave him the pieces back, and he paid me a good shilling—I sent information to the police.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Are you sure the prisoner is the person? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, he was there two or three minutes—I keep the Plough, in Lordship-lane—a great many persons come there, but there were none there then—I took particular notice of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1851" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1851" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1851" type="surname" value="MIDDLECOTT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1851" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE MIDDLECOTT</persName>
                  </hi>. My brother keeps the Greyhound, at Dulwich. On the 2nd of Aug., the prisoner came to his house—he had a pot of half and half, and gave me a bad half-crown—I gave it to my sister, and she bent it on the pewter—I gave it him back—he went into the tap room—he paid for his half and half with a good sixpence—I had seen bad money before—I am certain the half-crown was bad.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Had you seen him before? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—he was in the house an hour—I saw him for about five minutes at the bar.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1852" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1852" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1852" type="surname" value="SIMMONDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1852" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES SIMMONDS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable P</hi> 153.) I went to the Greyhound, on the 2nd of Aug., I found the prisoner there—I found a half-crown in his</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184308210245"></xptr>
               <p>pocket—I took him to the station—in taking off his boots I found two bad shillings, a sixpence, and one shilling, and a sixpence fell out which Trigg got.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1853" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1853" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1853" type="surname" value="TRIGG"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1853" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS TRIGG</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable P</hi> 262.) I was at the Greyhound—I took the man who was in company with the prisoner—the prisoner was searched by Simmonds—I picked up a shilling, and a sixpence which I saw fall out of his boot on the floor.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1854" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1854" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1854" type="surname" value="FIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1854" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>MR. JOHN FIELD</persName>
                  </hi>. These are all counterfeit.</p>
